This paper is primarily focused on the development of explainable AI, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed framework is neurally-inspired, which suggests a connection to neural networks and computational neuroscience (cs.NE). Additionally, the framework involves decision-making processes, which could be related to machine learning and decision theory (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the potential for AI failure in operating on imperfect data, which could be relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) and cybersecurity (cs.CR).
